From: Tim Eves <tim_eves@sil.org>
Date: Wed, 24 Aug 2011 20:53:26 +0700
Subject: [PATCH] Stop MSVC from spamming build logs

MSVC claims to have a performance problem with implicit cast to bool, however
since fixing that also improves code readability by 0.00000001% and stops tons
of annoying warning messages there seem no harm in adding this.
---
 src/Sparse.h | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/src/Sparse.h b/src/Sparse.h
index 841d0af8..9bb4c780 100644
--- a/src/Sparse.h
+++ b/src/Sparse.h
@@ -119,7 +119,7 @@ sparse::sparse(I attr, const I last)
 inline
 sparse::operator bool () const throw()
 {
-	return m_array.map;
+	return m_array.map != 0;
 }
 
 
